WEBVTT

00:00.001 --> 00:01.648
Shouldn't we wait for PJ to open this?

00:01.673 --> 00:03.812
You should know first
and be ready to help him

00:03.836 --> 00:05.085
with whatever the truth is.

00:05.110 --> 00:06.828
<i>DELILAH: Holding on to a secret...</i>

00:06.853 --> 00:09.232
- What are these?
- I have clinical depression.

00:09.257 --> 00:11.015
<i>... is like holding a grenade.</i>

00:11.040 --> 00:12.485
- Jon left you money.
- We don't want it.

00:12.509 --> 00:13.890
I don't want my son finding out

00:13.915 --> 00:15.624
that I've been lying
to him his whole life.

00:15.649 --> 00:16.804
<i>At any moment...</i>

00:16.829 --> 00:18.609
- I applied to RISD.
- You did, sweetie?

00:18.634 --> 00:20.008
Is there any way that you
guys could help me out?

00:20.032 --> 00:21.662
You know we don't have
that kind of money.

00:21.686 --> 00:22.766
<i>... your hand could slip...</i>

00:22.790 --> 00:23.821
EDDIE: I'm making the decision

00:23.845 --> 00:26.031
to be the best father
I can be for Charlie.

00:26.056 --> 00:28.101
That means being honest
with both of my children.

00:28.126 --> 00:29.321
- <i>... people could get hurt.</i>
- [LAUGHS]

00:29.345 --> 00:30.345
Oh, my God!

00:30.370 --> 00:32.654
I'm sorry. I-I'm so stupid.

00:32.679 --> 00:33.679
Are we okay?

00:33.704 --> 00:36.312
I'm still trying to figure
out who I am without cancer.

00:36.337 --> 00:37.695
<i>So maybe the answer...</i>

00:37.720 --> 00:40.664
I would be honored if you'd
go on that cruise with me.

00:40.689 --> 00:42.015
<i>... is to let the truth out.</i>

00:42.040 --> 00:43.640
Jon is PJ's father.

00:47.122 --> 00:49.429
ROME: You know what?
Maybe PJ will be excited.

00:49.454 --> 00:51.124
To learn his parents
have been lying to him

00:51.148 --> 00:52.459
since the day he was born?

00:52.460 --> 00:54.180
- Totally.
- I'm just saying, I'd be excited

00:54.204 --> 00:56.117
if I found out that my dad
wasn't really my dad.

00:56.142 --> 00:58.625
No, but seriously,
what if he's not excited?

00:58.680 --> 01:00.007
I don't know.

01:00.646 --> 01:01.805
It's a lot.

01:02.235 --> 01:03.835
- [CELLPHONE VIBRATES]
- Ugh.

01:03.860 --> 01:05.242
Is that your dad texting you

01:05.266 --> 01:06.571
to pick up more stuff for the cruise?

01:06.595 --> 01:07.968
The all-inclusive cruise?

01:07.993 --> 01:09.072
- Yes.
- [CHUCKLES]

01:09.097 --> 01:10.766
He wants thongs.

01:10.791 --> 01:12.450
He better be talking about flip-flops.

01:12.475 --> 01:13.531
[CHUCKLES]

01:13.556 --> 01:15.645
You know, honestly,
as worried as I am about PJ,

01:15.670 --> 01:17.960
I'm more worried about Delilah.

01:17.985 --> 01:19.742
When she finds out he's Jon's son...

01:19.767 --> 01:21.742
As if she doesn't have
enough kids on her plate.

01:22.314 --> 01:23.992
How do I tell her this?

01:24.765 --> 01:26.508
Well, if she's gonna be
okay hearing it from anyone,

01:26.532 --> 01:27.906
it's definitely gonna be you.

01:27.931 --> 01:29.000
You know what?

01:29.025 --> 01:31.898
How about you tell her while I tell PJ,

01:31.923 --> 01:34.031
then we'll meet back here
later tonight for booze?

01:34.056 --> 01:36.109
- [CHUCKLES]
- [CELLPHONE VIBRATES]

01:36.134 --> 01:38.125
My dad wants me to
pick up a prescription.

01:38.150 --> 01:39.445
What for?

01:39.766 --> 01:40.984
Oh, God!

01:41.009 --> 01:42.969
That's gonna be one hell of a cruise.

01:44.031 --> 01:45.320
- Oh!
- Oh, come on.

01:45.353 --> 01:47.022
- Oh, that's...
- [BOSTON ACCENT] My God.

01:47.047 --> 01:49.429
They are going crazy at the Garden.

01:49.454 --> 01:50.874
[NORMAL VOICE] What a comeback, people.

01:50.898 --> 01:53.125
Down by 10 to tie it up.

01:53.150 --> 01:55.015
- Next point wins.
- Alright.

01:55.040 --> 01:57.015
Whoa, time-out, time-out.
This is a dress sock.

01:57.040 --> 01:58.811
- Mm-hmm.
- While dressier, everyone knows

01:58.836 --> 01:59.992
they are far less aerodynamic.

02:00.016 --> 02:03.092
Oh, he's already starting
with the excuses, people.

02:03.117 --> 02:05.389
The true sign of a sore loser.

02:05.414 --> 02:07.061
- Okay, fine.
- Ooh, the pressure's on.

02:07.086 --> 02:08.756
He's feeling it. Yeah.

02:08.781 --> 02:10.068
There's a lot riding on this.

02:10.094 --> 02:12.133
There's a dog walk with
Colin, his manhood,

02:12.158 --> 02:14.616
and it's all rolled
up in one dress sock.

02:14.641 --> 02:16.600
- Jayson Tatum.
- Pfft.

02:16.625 --> 02:17.983
- Oh, no!
- Oh!

02:18.008 --> 02:19.242
- Oh, that's all basket!
- Please.

02:19.266 --> 02:21.046
That's a win for a winner,
which makes you a loser.

02:21.070 --> 02:22.819
You're a lose-stress. You've lost.

02:22.844 --> 02:24.367
Colin, you're gonna have
to do a number two with

02:24.391 --> 02:25.600
[LAUGHING] with number two.

02:25.625 --> 02:26.881
Ha ha. That's not even fair

02:26.906 --> 02:28.945
'cause you have that mini
Celtics hoop at your office.

02:28.969 --> 02:30.656
- [HIGH-PITCHED VOICE] Well, that's...
- Clearly, you're playing all day.

02:30.680 --> 02:32.078
[NORMAL VOICE] This is sad to listen to.

02:32.102 --> 02:34.000
It's even sadder if you
don't get him out of here.

02:34.024 --> 02:35.031
- That's a poop twirl.
- [COLIN WHINES]

02:35.055 --> 02:36.889
Oh, yeah. Oh, boy.

02:36.914 --> 02:38.022
[CELLPHONE VIBRATES]

02:38.047 --> 02:39.367
- Hello?
- Oh, that's probably

02:39.392 --> 02:41.953
The Globe calling for
a quote from the loser.

02:41.978 --> 02:43.859
Just tell them that you didn't execute.

02:44.532 --> 02:46.148
Uh, no.

02:46.712 --> 02:48.164
That's amazing. N... Yes.

02:48.189 --> 02:49.848
Yeah. I'm still interested.

02:49.873 --> 02:51.462
I'm very interested.

02:51.487 --> 02:53.922
Uh, can you hold on one second?

02:54.399 --> 02:55.399
Okay.

02:55.424 --> 02:56.507
[CELLPHONE BEEPS]

02:56.532 --> 02:58.867
That... That is a call from Oxford.

02:58.892 --> 03:00.562
- [CHUCKLES]
- Oxford?

03:00.587 --> 03:01.867
Oxford, Massachusetts?

03:01.892 --> 03:05.054
No, the lesser known one, in England.

03:05.079 --> 03:07.118
I applied for this teaching fellowship,

03:07.143 --> 03:09.148
uh, and I thought I had
no chance of getting it,

03:09.173 --> 03:12.414
but it sounds like maybe I'm
moving on to the next round.

03:13.242 --> 03:16.483
I know that you are the sock
basketball champion of the world,

03:16.508 --> 03:18.506
but can you please walk Colin?

03:18.829 --> 03:21.038
Yeah. Of course.

03:21.686 --> 03:24.288
Take the call, Bloom. Good luck.

03:24.313 --> 03:26.108
Hi. I'm so sorry.

03:26.133 --> 03:28.428
- No, no, this is a good time.
- Come on, buddy.

03:28.585 --> 03:30.545
- Yeah.
- Come on, Colin.

03:30.570 --> 03:34.225
I-I did my dissertation
on complicated bereavement

03:34.250 --> 03:36.022
back when I was in Chicago.

03:36.047 --> 03:38.225
Alright, Theo, Mom's waiting.

03:38.250 --> 03:41.061
Hurry up and brush your teeth...
Not just your front ones.

03:42.312 --> 03:43.319
Hey, do you have time

03:43.344 --> 03:45.506
to pick up a new sleeping
bag for him today?

03:45.531 --> 03:46.731
What's wrong with his old one?

03:47.133 --> 03:48.491
Apparently, he's blaming

03:48.516 --> 03:50.225
his failed sleepover attempt with Auggie

03:50.250 --> 03:51.631
on faulty equipment.

03:51.656 --> 03:53.624
- [BOTH LAUGH]
- That's amazing.

03:53.649 --> 03:55.725
I am supposed to watch Charlie today,

03:55.750 --> 03:58.686
but let me see how long
Delilah needs me.

03:58.711 --> 04:00.545
Oh. Look at that. She just texted.

04:00.570 --> 04:02.077
Looks like her plans got canceled.

04:02.102 --> 04:03.881
I can totally pick up the bag.

04:06.466 --> 04:07.705
What?

04:07.730 --> 04:08.866
N-Nothing.

04:08.891 --> 04:10.600
It's just...

04:10.625 --> 04:12.631
do you think her plans
really got canceled?

04:12.656 --> 04:13.959
Yeah. Why?

04:14.290 --> 04:15.975
Well, it's just...

04:16.848 --> 04:19.880
ever since we told her we want
to tell the kids the truth...

04:20.329 --> 04:21.709
I don't know. I just...

04:21.733 --> 04:24.039
hope this isn't a move
to keep you away from Charlie.

04:24.064 --> 04:27.008
No. I... don't think D would do that.

04:28.232 --> 04:30.493
Yeah, you're probably right.

04:30.518 --> 04:34.307
Hey, T, stop homeschooling
yourself and come downstairs.

04:34.332 --> 04:39.751
♪♪

04:39.788 --> 04:41.844
- Mom, it's here!
- RISD?

04:41.869 --> 04:43.039
Yeah.

04:45.734 --> 04:46.883
Wow, the envelope is big.

04:46.908 --> 04:48.719
That's usually a good sign, right?

04:49.602 --> 04:51.985
Come on, come on, come on,
come on, come on!

04:52.010 --> 04:53.391
"The Rhode Island School of Design

04:53.416 --> 04:54.602
is pleased to inform you"...

04:54.627 --> 04:56.250
I-I got in! [LAUGHS]

04:56.275 --> 04:58.883
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!
I'm so proud of you!

04:58.908 --> 04:59.908
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

04:59.933 --> 05:02.844
"After financial aid,
your expected family contribution

05:02.869 --> 05:04.360
for the first semester is...

05:05.016 --> 05:07.649
$14,580."

05:09.055 --> 05:10.789
Oh.

05:12.005 --> 05:13.547
Oh, sweetie.

05:13.572 --> 05:15.875
I know. We can't afford it.

05:18.755 --> 05:20.078
What's all the excitement?

05:20.103 --> 05:22.422
- Nothing.
- Patrick.

05:22.447 --> 05:26.758
♪♪

05:26.783 --> 05:29.493
ROME: Hey, Pop. Got your pills.

05:29.518 --> 05:30.680
Thanks for that.

05:30.705 --> 05:32.141
Did you get my flip-flops?

05:32.166 --> 05:33.835
Yes. Both pairs.

05:33.860 --> 05:35.461
Why do you need two of these?

05:35.486 --> 05:37.649
- These are great. Thanks, Pop.
- Mm-hmm.

05:37.674 --> 05:39.040
ROME: Omar, what are you doing here?

05:39.064 --> 05:40.930
- House-sitting.
- You mean freeloading?

05:40.955 --> 05:42.874
Not freeloading. He's getting paid.

05:42.899 --> 05:43.931
He's getting... Okay, great.

05:43.955 --> 05:45.795
Well, maybe he can help you
figure out your new phone.

05:45.819 --> 05:48.024
I tried already. Can't figure it out.

05:48.049 --> 05:49.578
Oh, oh!

05:49.991 --> 05:51.735
Let me see the phone, please.

05:51.760 --> 05:54.024
That damn thing came
with free headphones.

05:54.049 --> 05:56.098
You get my voicemail to
work, they're yours.

05:56.123 --> 05:58.250
Actually, that's great,
'cause mine just broke.

05:58.275 --> 05:59.695
- [HIP-HOP MUSIC PLAYS IN HEADPHONES]
- Hey, these are great.

05:59.719 --> 06:01.125
Hey, Pop, can I have these?

06:01.537 --> 06:03.352
Just let your brother have them.

06:03.377 --> 06:05.204
Can't he just buy his own
with the money he's getting

06:05.228 --> 06:06.969
for house-sitting the
house he grew up in?

06:06.994 --> 06:08.750
♪ Work, work, work ♪

06:08.775 --> 06:11.669
- [FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]
- How are my boys doing in here?

06:11.694 --> 06:12.694
Hey, Ma.

06:12.719 --> 06:13.857
- Hey, Mom.
- [CHUCKLES]

06:13.882 --> 06:16.396
Thanks for picking up all
the stuff for the cruise.

06:16.421 --> 06:17.841
I can always count on you.

06:17.866 --> 06:18.995
Thank you, Mom.

06:19.020 --> 06:20.654
See you still rocking
that captain's hat.

06:20.679 --> 06:23.037
Well, just until I get
my hair done later.

06:23.062 --> 06:25.404
Regina was so sweet to
make me an appointment.

06:25.429 --> 06:27.873
Someone wants to look
nice for the captain.

06:27.898 --> 06:31.310
He has personally invited us to dinner.

06:31.335 --> 06:35.412
- Sure. But I am not wearing a tie.
- You are wearing a tie.

06:35.437 --> 06:37.638
I laid out the nice red one on the bed.

06:37.663 --> 06:39.419
It makes you look dapper.

06:41.912 --> 06:43.465
What are these?

06:43.490 --> 06:45.552
I didn't want the ones
that separate the big toe.

06:45.577 --> 06:46.873
I can't wear socks with these.

06:46.898 --> 06:49.060
Walter, you can buy them on board.

06:49.085 --> 06:50.287
Sure.

06:51.041 --> 06:53.123
Give your captain friend more money.

06:54.896 --> 06:57.543
You know, Mom,
if he were to suddenly fall overboard,

06:57.568 --> 06:59.489
I'm sure we could convince
the jury it was an accident.

06:59.490 --> 07:01.927
[CHUCKLES] I know he's a lot,

07:01.952 --> 07:05.169
but I wish you and your dad
could find a way to get along.

07:05.770 --> 07:07.552
Promise me you'll try.

07:08.285 --> 07:10.209
- I'll try.
- Thank you.

07:15.178 --> 07:19.005
So, I made those changes you
wanted to the catering menu.

07:19.030 --> 07:21.802
You want to just look and see
if it's the layout you wanted?

07:23.430 --> 07:25.990
Yeah. But before we do that...

07:26.250 --> 07:28.623
I really need to talk
to you about something.

07:29.900 --> 07:32.599
I'm sorry if I've been
a little short with you.

07:32.624 --> 07:35.185
It's just I've been feeling ganged-up on

07:35.210 --> 07:37.037
about all this Charlie stuff.

07:37.062 --> 07:38.388
I hear that, but...

07:38.413 --> 07:40.677
I don't understand why all of a sudden

07:40.702 --> 07:42.380
you would take Eddie
and Katherine's side.

07:42.405 --> 07:45.115
It's... You're my best friend.

07:45.830 --> 07:47.896
I know, D.

07:48.471 --> 07:51.010
I don't want you
to feel that way, but...

07:51.035 --> 07:53.044
[SIGHS] being a best
friend doesn't always mean

07:53.069 --> 07:54.988
telling you what you want to hear.

07:55.013 --> 07:58.232
Sometimes it's telling you
what y-you need to hear.

07:59.587 --> 08:02.498
Which is why this is really difficult.

08:03.810 --> 08:06.231
[CELLPHONE VIBRATING]

08:06.256 --> 08:08.060
Oh, God. It's the salon.

08:09.082 --> 08:11.412
I hope they didn't fry
my mother-in-law's hair.

08:11.437 --> 08:13.498
- [CELLPHONE BEEPS]
- This is Regina.

08:13.523 --> 08:14.892
[SCOFFS] Wow.

08:14.917 --> 08:16.126
[SIGHS]

08:16.549 --> 08:17.549
[SCOFFS]

08:17.574 --> 08:20.060
♪ She droppin' now,
'cause we poppin' now ♪

08:20.085 --> 08:22.560
Just take the headphones, man.
They're not that great.

08:22.585 --> 08:23.717
It's not about the headphones, okay?

08:23.741 --> 08:25.620
It's about Dad always taking your side.

08:25.645 --> 08:27.443
It's like the bunk beds all over again.

08:27.468 --> 08:28.990
Bu... Oh... Oh, my God!

08:29.015 --> 08:31.396
It was 30 years ago! Get over it!

08:31.421 --> 08:32.904
Says the guy who got the top bunk.

08:32.929 --> 08:34.350
If you hadn't have got the bottom bunk,

08:34.374 --> 08:36.374
you never would have hooked
up with Tania Peterson.

08:36.804 --> 08:38.287
She was a nerd...

08:38.548 --> 08:40.498
but she was a nerd with boobs.

08:40.614 --> 08:42.573
If I got anywhere
with Tania, it's because

08:42.599 --> 08:44.748
Mom put those glow-in-the-dark
stars over my bed.

08:44.773 --> 08:47.682
So... So Mom was pimping for you,
but I'm the favorite.

08:47.872 --> 08:50.052
WALTER: Rome, you forgot my orthotics!

08:50.077 --> 08:51.755
See? You done ticked off Daddy.

08:51.780 --> 08:53.925
Unbelievable.

08:54.145 --> 08:56.145
[SIGHS]

08:58.518 --> 09:00.482
- [DOOR CLOSES]
- Hey, what are you doing here?

09:02.549 --> 09:03.968
Oh, no.

09:03.993 --> 09:05.532
Did D not take the news well?

09:05.557 --> 09:07.474
I-I didn't get a chance to tell her.

09:07.499 --> 09:08.983
Yeah, I hadn't had a chance
to talk to PJ, either,

09:09.007 --> 09:10.959
because I've been too
busy disappointing my dad.

09:10.984 --> 09:12.482
- Rome...
- I don't even know why

09:12.507 --> 09:14.005
I try getting along with him...

09:14.030 --> 09:15.038
My old man is who he is...

09:15.062 --> 09:16.811
'cause nothing is ever
gonna change that.

09:16.836 --> 09:18.794
Baby, uh...

09:19.357 --> 09:20.701
What's wrong?

09:22.652 --> 09:24.490
Your mom died.

09:24.515 --> 09:28.732
♪♪

09:28.757 --> 09:33.757
Synced & corrected by QueenMaddie
www.addic7ed.com

09:40.860 --> 09:41.998
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

09:42.023 --> 09:43.392
An aneurysm?

09:43.417 --> 09:45.296
How is that possible?

09:45.321 --> 09:49.982
The doctor saw her a month
ago and said she was great.

09:50.472 --> 09:54.232
For what it's worth,
they said she went...

09:54.723 --> 09:58.029
quickly, without any pain.

09:58.715 --> 10:00.300
I can't believe this.

10:00.325 --> 10:02.914
She was just here a few hours ago.

10:02.939 --> 10:05.621
Should've seen how excited she
was to go on that cruise, Gina.

10:05.646 --> 10:07.152
It's so unfair.

10:07.177 --> 10:08.676
She was the glue.

10:08.701 --> 10:12.174
Uh... she held us all together.

10:12.346 --> 10:14.019
Especially Dad.

10:17.566 --> 10:19.025
Who's gonna tell him?

10:19.050 --> 10:23.589
♪♪

10:23.614 --> 10:25.613
I don't even know what to say.

10:25.638 --> 10:31.248
♪♪

10:31.273 --> 10:32.653
I'll do it.

10:34.505 --> 10:35.832
You sure?

10:37.333 --> 10:40.777
The last thing Mom said before
she walked out of that door was that...

10:43.504 --> 10:45.855
... she wanted me and Pop to get along.

10:47.545 --> 10:49.004
That starts right now.

10:57.646 --> 10:59.146
[SNIFFLES]

11:00.887 --> 11:03.253
[EXHALES SHARPLY] Thank you.

11:03.595 --> 11:05.113
[CLEARS THROAT]

11:06.420 --> 11:08.009
[SNIFFLES]

11:17.977 --> 11:18.977
Dad?

11:19.587 --> 11:21.675
Would you show your brother
how to work the remote?

11:21.700 --> 11:24.400
I don't want him erasing
my shows while I'm gone.

11:24.425 --> 11:25.544
Can you stop for a second?

11:25.545 --> 11:26.825
I have something to tell you, Pop.

11:26.849 --> 11:28.439
There's nothing you have to tell me.

11:28.464 --> 11:29.613
I have to pack.

11:29.638 --> 11:33.128
And to be honest, this suitcase
you got us, not that great.

11:33.153 --> 11:35.222
Can you please listen?

11:37.355 --> 11:38.545
[VOICE BREAKING] Mom...

11:43.100 --> 11:45.159
She died, Pop.

11:47.666 --> 11:49.246
I know.

11:49.795 --> 11:52.174
I heard you all talking downstairs.

11:53.020 --> 11:54.020
[SIGHS]

11:54.045 --> 11:55.700
I don't understand.
If you... If you heard us,

11:55.724 --> 11:57.400
then what... what are you doing?

11:57.425 --> 11:58.802
Packing.

11:59.345 --> 12:00.841
It might sound crazy,

12:00.866 --> 12:04.230
but I promised your mother
I would go on that cruise.

12:04.255 --> 12:09.584
♪♪

12:09.585 --> 12:12.464
And I'm keeping my promise to her.

12:12.465 --> 12:17.634
♪♪

12:17.635 --> 12:18.748
[ZIPPER OPENS]

12:18.773 --> 12:21.841
Oh, thank you so much for
lending me the Bonnie Ray CD.

12:21.866 --> 12:24.380
- She's amazing.
- I don't know who this "Bonnie Ray" is,

12:24.405 --> 12:26.480
but Bonnie Raitt is amazing.

12:26.505 --> 12:27.654
I'm 16.

12:27.679 --> 12:29.771
How am I supposed to know
who all those old people are?

12:29.795 --> 12:32.583
- Okay. Wow.
- [LAUGHS]

12:32.608 --> 12:35.187
Next week's lesson, we're gonna
start with some music history.

12:35.212 --> 12:37.884
I'm not sure I'm gonna
be here next week.

12:37.909 --> 12:40.636
Actually, this might be
my last lesson for a while

12:40.661 --> 12:42.754
'cause Mom's thinking of taking me,
Danny, and Charlie

12:42.778 --> 12:44.371
to France for the summer.

12:44.396 --> 12:45.706
- France?
- Yeah.

12:45.731 --> 12:47.320
Wow. That's...

12:47.651 --> 12:48.761
When did this happen?

12:48.786 --> 12:50.276
Uh, this morning.

12:50.301 --> 12:52.090
Yeah, she kind of sprung it on us,

12:52.115 --> 12:55.214
but she was up all night last
night looking at airfares.

12:55.888 --> 12:57.017
[CHUCKLES]

12:57.042 --> 12:59.644
♪♪

12:59.669 --> 13:01.112
[DOOR CLOSES]

13:01.909 --> 13:03.808
Hi, boy. Hi, bud.

13:03.833 --> 13:07.839
Phew. How's, uh, jolly old England?

13:07.864 --> 13:09.979
Heh. I assume that
was the Queen calling.

13:10.004 --> 13:12.105
Oh, yeah. That was,
in fact, the Queen calling.

13:12.130 --> 13:17.190
Uh, Her Majesty wanted me to be
sure to tell you, "Whazzuuuupp."

13:17.215 --> 13:19.683
- How 1997 of her.
- [CHUCKLES]

13:19.708 --> 13:23.792
Look, um... I applied for this
fellowship before I got sick.

13:23.817 --> 13:26.245
Wow. Mail to England is really slow.

13:26.270 --> 13:28.690
I got accepted last time...

13:29.660 --> 13:33.369
but then when I got
my diagnosis, I deferred,

13:33.394 --> 13:36.267
and I contacted them a few weeks ago

13:36.292 --> 13:37.877
to see if there is any possibility

13:37.902 --> 13:39.369
that they would still consider me.

13:39.394 --> 13:40.604
A few weeks ago?

13:43.010 --> 13:44.042
Why didn't you say anything?

13:44.066 --> 13:45.643
'Cause I didn't think
there was any chance

13:45.667 --> 13:47.205
that they would say yes.

13:47.230 --> 13:48.385
And they haven't yet.

13:48.410 --> 13:50.470
But apparently someone dropped out,

13:50.495 --> 13:52.010
and a spot opened up,

13:52.035 --> 13:54.447
and they want to video-chat this week.

13:54.472 --> 13:57.641
Alright. Well, this is very exciting.

13:57.698 --> 13:59.528
So, how long is this fellowship?

14:01.027 --> 14:03.267
It's a year.

14:04.494 --> 14:06.823
That's longer than
we've known each other.

14:06.848 --> 14:08.752
I mean, it's not really that long.

14:08.777 --> 14:10.816
It's what, 12 months?

14:10.841 --> 14:12.502
And with the holidays,

14:12.527 --> 14:15.103
r-really, December doesn't even count,

14:15.128 --> 14:17.447
and then there's spring
break and Thanksgiving

14:17.472 --> 14:19.424
and Boxing Day, whatever that is.

14:19.449 --> 14:20.450
- [CELLPHONE VIBRATES]
- [LAUGHS]

14:20.474 --> 14:21.628
Forgive me if I'm not quite ready

14:21.652 --> 14:23.181
to make jokes about this.

14:23.206 --> 14:25.510
- [CELLPHONE BEEPS]
- Hey, D, what's up?

14:27.541 --> 14:29.142
His mom?

14:30.111 --> 14:32.080
Soph, if you are here next week,

14:32.105 --> 14:34.455
we're gonna be learning
a little Stevie Nicks,

14:34.962 --> 14:36.580
who, despite the name, is a woman.

14:36.605 --> 14:38.065
SOPHIE: [LAUGHS] Thanks.

14:41.613 --> 14:43.193
[DOOR CLOSES]

14:45.054 --> 14:48.111
Okay, so, this France thing
doesn't seem great.

14:49.206 --> 14:52.322
I mean, Charlie just started
recognizing my voice,

14:52.347 --> 14:54.752
and I swear she smiles
when she sees me now.

14:54.777 --> 14:56.857
Who knows what she's gonna be
doing by the end of the summer.

14:56.881 --> 14:59.049
That's a long time to be away.

15:01.318 --> 15:02.877
I'm sorry.

15:03.641 --> 15:06.213
You're the last person I
should be complaining to.

15:06.238 --> 15:07.494
She's your daughter.

15:07.519 --> 15:09.220
You have every right to be upset.

15:09.245 --> 15:12.228
It's like I don't even have
a say in Charlie's life.

15:13.009 --> 15:15.128
[SIGHS] Can she do that?

15:15.153 --> 15:17.283
Well, yeah, she can, if...

15:19.228 --> 15:21.861
If what?

15:22.971 --> 15:26.658
I don't even know
if I should... ask this.

15:27.096 --> 15:30.720
But to get a passport for a baby,

15:30.745 --> 15:33.299
you need to have a birth certificate.

15:34.339 --> 15:36.588
Do you know if you're
listed on Charlie's?

15:38.790 --> 15:40.329
What do you mean he's still going?

15:40.354 --> 15:43.183
He promised Mom he
would go on that cruise.

15:43.457 --> 15:44.767
Oh.

15:44.951 --> 15:47.338
Well, what about the funeral?

15:47.363 --> 15:50.470
He says he wants us to
do it before he leaves.

15:50.495 --> 15:52.181
Said Mom never wanted us

15:52.206 --> 15:54.345
to spend a lot of money on the service.

15:54.370 --> 15:56.986
Um, the cruise is in a couple of days.

15:57.011 --> 15:59.650
He wants us to put together
a funeral before that?

15:59.675 --> 16:00.845
Here's what I know.

16:01.470 --> 16:04.314
Dad and I both made promises to Mom...

16:05.145 --> 16:07.377
Promises I plan on keeping.

16:09.914 --> 16:11.744
Then that's what we're gonna do.

16:11.769 --> 16:18.769
♪♪

16:21.280 --> 16:24.447
ROME: Two days ago,
when I kissed my mother goodbye,

16:24.763 --> 16:27.682
I never thought it'd be
the last time I'd see her.

16:27.707 --> 16:32.206
♪♪

16:32.231 --> 16:33.947
She had tuna fish breath.

16:33.972 --> 16:36.352
[LAUGHTER]

16:37.253 --> 16:39.205
It's true. [SNIFFLES]

16:39.230 --> 16:40.931
She loved her tuna fish.

16:41.454 --> 16:44.203
But as sad as I am to
say goodbye to you,

16:44.228 --> 16:46.439
there's nothing else I needed to say,

16:46.644 --> 16:51.322
and there's... nothing else I
needed to hear you say to me.

16:52.762 --> 16:53.971
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

16:53.996 --> 16:57.752
It's such a blessed
place to be with someone.

17:02.221 --> 17:04.924
Thank you for always looking out for me.

17:07.721 --> 17:09.588
I love you, Mom.

17:10.042 --> 17:12.032
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

17:12.058 --> 17:13.877
And I miss you already.

17:13.902 --> 17:20.902
♪♪

17:20.926 --> 17:27.926
♪♪

17:27.952 --> 17:30.122
[SOBBING]

17:30.677 --> 17:34.426
♪♪

17:34.451 --> 17:36.098
I'm gonna wait in the car.

17:36.123 --> 17:37.606
I'm sorry.

17:37.631 --> 17:43.161
♪♪

17:43.290 --> 17:45.159
It was nice of him to come.

17:45.184 --> 17:47.208
He wanted to be here for you.

17:47.233 --> 17:49.208
- I have to tell him.
- Not today.

17:49.233 --> 17:52.966
Today's about...
saying goodbye to your mother.

17:53.698 --> 17:55.364
He'll understand.

17:59.868 --> 18:02.161
That was really beautiful, man.
[SNIFFLES]

18:02.186 --> 18:03.506
Except for the part where the minister

18:03.530 --> 18:06.309
was saying the final prayer
and my dad's phone goes off.

18:06.334 --> 18:07.763
The only thing louder than a ringtone

18:07.787 --> 18:09.997
is an old man trying
to turn off a ringtone.

18:10.474 --> 18:11.762
[CHUCKLES]

18:11.787 --> 18:13.207
I love you, man.

18:14.279 --> 18:15.747
Love you, bro.

18:16.361 --> 18:18.520
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

18:21.349 --> 18:23.308
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

18:32.708 --> 18:35.145
MAN: She did.
She had a wonderful personality.

18:35.170 --> 18:36.965
Was always so kind.

18:36.990 --> 18:40.329
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

18:40.354 --> 18:47.354
♪♪

18:47.379 --> 18:52.965
♪♪

18:52.990 --> 18:54.512
[JACKET THUDS]

18:54.537 --> 19:01.537
♪♪

19:01.562 --> 19:08.562
♪♪

19:08.587 --> 19:15.587
♪♪

19:16.356 --> 19:18.106
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

19:22.692 --> 19:24.912
- You should dye your hair pink.
- I think that's important.

19:24.936 --> 19:26.012
EDDIE: Hey.

19:26.037 --> 19:27.231
Hey, guys. Hi.

19:27.521 --> 19:30.536
That was really beautiful,
what you guys did up there.

19:30.561 --> 19:32.481
Yeah, we couldn't let
Rome do it on his own.

19:32.506 --> 19:33.654
We would've been here all day.

19:33.678 --> 19:34.949
Hmm.

19:34.974 --> 19:36.676
Hey, can I talk to you for a sec?

19:36.701 --> 19:37.701
Sure.

19:39.878 --> 19:42.926
So, Sophie said something
about you guys going to France.

19:43.327 --> 19:46.629
Yeah, I was just... thinking about it.

19:46.654 --> 19:50.684
It might be fun for the kids
to see where I grew up,

19:50.709 --> 19:52.161
meet some of my relatives,

19:52.186 --> 19:54.606
maybe brush up on
their nonexistent French.

19:55.271 --> 19:58.028
And this doesn't have anything
to do with Katherine and I

19:58.053 --> 19:59.520
wanting to tell the kids the truth?

19:59.545 --> 20:01.106
- Eddie, what...
- D, if you are going

20:01.131 --> 20:02.707
to take Charlie to France,

20:02.732 --> 20:05.111
don't you think you need to
talk to me about that first?

20:05.136 --> 20:07.193
I mean, you say you want me
to be a part of her life,

20:07.217 --> 20:08.731
but you're not really acting like it.

20:08.756 --> 20:11.317
How can you say that? Of course I do.

20:11.342 --> 20:13.817
That's why I ran her name by you first.

20:13.842 --> 20:15.348
It's why I did that photo shoot

20:15.373 --> 20:17.387
to get you in her birth announcement.

20:17.412 --> 20:19.661
Eddie, I'm doing everything I can.

20:19.686 --> 20:21.684
And I appreciate it.

20:22.299 --> 20:24.215
But let me ask you this.

20:24.240 --> 20:27.692
Who is listed as the father on
Charlie's birth certificate?

20:28.072 --> 20:30.122
You know it's Jon.

20:30.505 --> 20:32.106
Eddie, correct me if I'm wrong,

20:32.131 --> 20:34.481
but this was the plan we agreed to.

20:34.667 --> 20:35.667
Yeah.

20:36.388 --> 20:39.137
But I guess what I didn't plan on...

20:39.752 --> 20:41.739
was feeling this way.

20:43.209 --> 20:48.997
♪♪

20:49.022 --> 20:50.606
What's the holdup?

20:51.301 --> 20:52.575
We're waiting on Gina.

20:52.600 --> 20:54.840
And make sure gets the
flowers and the pictures.

20:55.378 --> 20:56.770
Hey.

20:57.503 --> 20:59.590
About what you did back there...

21:00.159 --> 21:01.348
Yeah?

21:02.073 --> 21:03.107
I wish you would've told me

21:03.131 --> 21:04.357
you were gonna do all that shoveling.

21:04.381 --> 21:06.260
I wouldn't have paid
the guy to fill it in.

21:06.853 --> 21:10.643
You're gonna get dirt all over
your fancy, battery-powered car.

21:12.065 --> 21:14.668
Gina, what's the holdup?

21:15.536 --> 21:17.575
So, if Delilah took
Charlie out of the country

21:17.600 --> 21:18.832
and decided not to come back,

21:18.857 --> 21:20.465
there's nothing I could do about it?

21:20.490 --> 21:22.037
Well, not if you're not
on the birth certificate.

21:22.061 --> 21:23.895
[SIGHS]

21:23.920 --> 21:26.817
But I just... I can't imagine
she'd do that. [SCOFFS]

21:26.842 --> 21:28.918
I don't know, Eddie.

21:29.783 --> 21:32.911
And I really hope it
doesn't come to this.

21:32.936 --> 21:35.395
I make a living standing up for people,

21:35.760 --> 21:37.426
and right now,

21:37.451 --> 21:39.610
that's you and Charlie.

21:39.635 --> 21:46.764
♪♪

21:46.789 --> 21:48.459
You are amazing.

21:50.212 --> 21:51.864
We're in this together.

21:51.889 --> 21:56.606
♪♪

21:56.631 --> 21:58.551
[SIGHS] Thank you for taking these.

21:58.576 --> 21:59.995
Of course.

22:00.020 --> 22:01.639
Between Walter and Omar

22:01.664 --> 22:03.623
[CHUCKLES] it seems like
your hands are full.

22:03.648 --> 22:05.227
[CHUCKLES] They're pretty full.

22:05.408 --> 22:06.889
Where's Maggie?

22:06.908 --> 22:08.412
She went ahead with Delilah.

22:08.437 --> 22:11.061
That woman's bladder
is as tiny as she is.

22:11.086 --> 22:13.052
- [CAR ALARM BEEPS, DISENGAGES]
- Does this thing unhook, or...?

22:13.076 --> 22:18.077
♪♪

22:18.078 --> 22:20.131
Why is your work stuff...

22:22.423 --> 22:24.014
Oh, my God.

22:24.581 --> 22:25.982
You were fired?

22:26.788 --> 22:27.788
WALTER: Gina!

22:27.813 --> 22:29.139
Are we leaving, or do I need

22:29.164 --> 22:31.084
- to put my shoes back on?
- [SIGHS]

22:34.804 --> 22:38.607
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

22:38.632 --> 22:43.001
Ah, the culinary mystery
that is the puff pastry.

22:43.026 --> 22:44.525
What is it?

22:44.550 --> 22:46.764
A puff? A pastry?

22:46.789 --> 22:49.068
You got... one nipple, like me.

22:49.093 --> 22:50.093
- Gary?
- Yes?

22:50.118 --> 22:51.366
- Can I have those, please? Please?
- Sure.

22:51.390 --> 22:52.390
Thank you.

22:52.791 --> 22:54.490
Thank you for all your help.

22:54.515 --> 22:55.884
Of course.

22:55.909 --> 22:57.803
Oh, um, can you drop me
back at the apartment

22:57.828 --> 22:59.037
so I can do the interview,

22:59.062 --> 23:01.154
or do you need to
check in at the office?

23:01.179 --> 23:02.451
I'm all yours.

23:02.476 --> 23:03.881
Mm. Thank you.

23:04.933 --> 23:07.397
Uh, why haven't you told Maggie?

23:07.422 --> 23:08.990
Because my bosses weren't thrilled

23:09.015 --> 23:10.889
with how much time I took off this year.

23:10.914 --> 23:11.865
I mean, did you tell them

23:11.890 --> 23:13.709
that you were busy
saving someone's life?

23:13.734 --> 23:16.773
Apparently they only care
about the lives they insure.

23:16.798 --> 23:19.857
Well, still... you have to tell her.

23:19.882 --> 23:21.107
I will.

23:21.132 --> 23:24.350
The thing is, she applied for
some fellowship at Oxford.

23:24.375 --> 23:25.506
[CHUCKLES]

23:25.531 --> 23:26.670
Yeah, that Oxford.

23:27.061 --> 23:28.749
Anyway, it's a big opportunity for her,
you know?

23:28.773 --> 23:30.116
I don't want this to
affect her decision.

23:30.140 --> 23:32.865
So, please... please don't say anything.

23:32.890 --> 23:37.131
♪♪

23:37.156 --> 23:40.529
[SOBBING] I don't know what
I'm gonna do without her.

23:40.554 --> 23:41.678
- Be right back.
- Yeah.

23:41.703 --> 23:43.242
- Get over there.
- It's... It's okay.

23:43.617 --> 23:46.623
Hey, Rome, I really need
to ask you a question,

23:46.648 --> 23:48.365
but I have to ask it way over there.

23:48.390 --> 23:49.990
- Yes, absolutely.
- Oh.

23:50.015 --> 23:51.701
Can... Can you excuse me, Joyce?

23:52.077 --> 23:53.318
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

23:53.343 --> 23:56.014
- You okay?
- I'm better now. Thank you.

23:56.039 --> 23:57.904
Alright. So, D, those are...

23:57.929 --> 23:59.338
That tray's for the roof.

23:59.363 --> 24:00.834
Oh, but on second thought,

24:00.859 --> 24:02.920
your dad may not be able
to make it up the steps.

24:02.945 --> 24:05.709
Jicama? I don't think so.

24:05.734 --> 24:07.023
Well, if you need me,

24:07.048 --> 24:08.920
I'll be on the roof for
the rest of the night.

24:08.945 --> 24:10.275
[CHUCKLES]

24:11.430 --> 24:13.679
I'm sorry, D, what...
What were you saying?

24:13.704 --> 24:15.186
No, I'm sorry.

24:15.211 --> 24:17.154
I shouldn't be bothering
you with any of this.

24:17.179 --> 24:20.411
It's just Eddie got me
upset at the cemetery,

24:20.436 --> 24:22.725
like I was keeping it from him.

24:22.750 --> 24:25.264
He all but accused me
of trying to run away.

24:26.735 --> 24:28.655
Well, are you?

24:31.241 --> 24:32.865
I-I mean, you said

24:32.890 --> 24:35.490
you were kind of feeling
ganged-up on lately.

24:35.689 --> 24:37.389
Makes sense that you want to get away.

24:37.414 --> 24:39.365
That's... That's all I'm saying.

24:45.944 --> 24:48.571
GARY: Sorry to hear
about you and Stasia.

24:48.775 --> 24:51.024
You two seemed so good together.

24:51.049 --> 24:52.602
Yeah, yeah. You know, me too, man.

24:52.627 --> 24:54.743
But, you know, it just went south,

24:54.768 --> 24:56.345
and not in a good way.

24:56.370 --> 25:00.029
It's like all of a sudden,
we just were on different pages.

25:00.054 --> 25:02.079
It's like one of those
couples on that design show.

25:02.104 --> 25:03.454
- Ooh, which one?
- The good one.

25:03.479 --> 25:04.673
The one with the twins.

25:04.698 --> 25:07.727
There's always that couple who, like,

25:07.752 --> 25:09.837
can't decide what house
they want to get together.

25:09.862 --> 25:11.521
- Mm. Mm-hmm.
- You know, and then, you know,

25:11.522 --> 25:13.188
one always wants the move-in ready...

25:13.213 --> 25:15.579
The other wants a fixer-upper
with a lot of work.

25:15.604 --> 25:17.141
- E-E-Exactly.
- Yeah. Yeah.

25:17.166 --> 25:18.619
No idea what you two are talking about.

25:18.643 --> 25:19.853
- It's fine.
- Yeah, it's a show, man.

25:19.877 --> 25:21.720
- You gotta check it out.
- Yeah.

25:21.745 --> 25:24.438
It's like at first, we wanted
the same thing, but...

25:25.265 --> 25:26.384
then it's just like

25:26.409 --> 25:28.735
we grew in different
directions, you know?

25:30.228 --> 25:33.071
Plus, she was into
some real freaky stuff.

25:33.096 --> 25:34.595
Mm.

25:34.759 --> 25:35.772
[GLASS THUDS]

25:35.797 --> 25:36.954
I'm talking about sex.

25:36.979 --> 25:37.979
- Yeah.
- Yep. Yep.

25:38.004 --> 25:39.407
- We made that leap.
- Yeah.

25:40.815 --> 25:46.024
♪♪

25:46.049 --> 25:47.260
Hey, do you know if those sandwiches

25:47.284 --> 25:48.744
are... are turkey or ham?

25:51.360 --> 25:52.759
Oh. [CHUCKLES]

25:52.784 --> 25:54.204
Duh.

25:54.901 --> 25:56.946
Uh, are the carrots any good?

25:57.808 --> 25:59.665
They're carrots.

25:59.821 --> 26:01.915
Okay, I-I feel like you're mad at me.

26:01.949 --> 26:03.376
Are you mad at me?

26:03.401 --> 26:04.570
Why would I be mad?

26:04.595 --> 26:06.040
I-I-I don't know.

26:06.065 --> 26:08.385
I just... I just feel like
you've been avoiding me all day.

26:08.472 --> 26:10.055
Where? The funeral?

26:10.080 --> 26:12.063
Yeah, there's a lot going on right now.

26:12.471 --> 26:14.720
[SIGHS] Sophie, listen,

26:14.745 --> 26:16.610
I-I think you're amazing.

26:16.635 --> 26:18.224
Please, just don't.

26:18.515 --> 26:21.110
Look, I get it. You told me
you just want to be friends.

26:21.135 --> 26:22.142
You don't have to keep telling me.

26:22.166 --> 26:23.596
Sophie, it's...
Look, it's not what you think.

26:23.620 --> 26:25.709
- I-I...
- Okay, look, I'm fine, alright?

26:26.155 --> 26:27.923
Let's not make this a
bigger deal than it is.

26:27.948 --> 26:29.037
[PLATE CLATTERS]

26:29.062 --> 26:31.761
[FOOTSTEPS DEPARTING]

26:31.786 --> 26:34.040
♪♪

26:34.065 --> 26:35.934
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

26:35.959 --> 26:37.459
[DOOR OPENS]

26:40.540 --> 26:43.212
Hi, Soph. Everything okay?

26:43.354 --> 26:45.103
Yeah, I'm fine.

26:46.714 --> 26:48.946
Did something happen with PJ?

26:49.818 --> 26:51.165
It's nothing.

26:53.774 --> 26:56.193
Okay, you know what?
You don't have to tell me.

26:56.218 --> 26:58.532
I'm just gonna sit here until you do.

27:01.484 --> 27:04.173
[HIGH-PITCHED] Mm, mm,
mm, mm, mm, mm, mm.

27:04.198 --> 27:05.977
[CHUCKLES] Okay, okay, alright.

27:06.002 --> 27:07.131
You're crushing me.

27:07.156 --> 27:08.352
[CHUCKLES]

27:08.377 --> 27:10.087
[SIGHS]

27:11.360 --> 27:13.095
I tried to kiss him.

27:14.542 --> 27:17.407
Yeah, that's how I got
into that accident.

27:17.432 --> 27:20.032
Oh. Soph.

27:20.242 --> 27:22.901
It's... It's just that
he backed away so fast,

27:22.926 --> 27:25.345
like I-I was the grossest
thing in the world.

27:25.900 --> 27:27.641
Come here.

27:29.748 --> 27:31.497
I know I'm your mother,

27:31.522 --> 27:33.970
and I know that you think I'm biased,

27:33.995 --> 27:36.587
but trust me when I tell you that...

27:37.226 --> 27:39.915
you're not the grossest
thing in the world.

27:39.940 --> 27:41.359
Not even top five.

27:41.384 --> 27:42.503
[CHUCKLES]

27:42.528 --> 27:44.712
[CHUCKLES]

27:44.737 --> 27:46.066
[SIGHS]

27:46.091 --> 27:48.813
Can we please just go to France already?

27:52.687 --> 27:55.727
I believe this American Girl
doll coat belongs to you.

27:55.752 --> 27:57.346
- [CHUCKLES]
- After I get this one home,

27:57.370 --> 27:58.915
should I swing back, check on our man?

27:58.940 --> 28:00.915
No, I got it.

28:01.501 --> 28:03.962
I just wish I could flip a
switch and make it better.

28:03.987 --> 28:05.612
I know. But all we do can

28:05.637 --> 28:07.188
is help him keep his head above water.

28:07.213 --> 28:10.962
You guys have been amazing
these last couple days.

28:10.987 --> 28:12.807
Apparently before this,
we were horrible friends.

28:12.831 --> 28:14.602
Mm-hmm. Yeah. [LAUGHS]

28:14.627 --> 28:16.321
I love you. Bye.

28:17.860 --> 28:20.735
[SIGHS] Okay.

28:20.760 --> 28:21.962
I mean, those twins,

28:21.987 --> 28:24.501
they just have so much
chemistry as brothers.

28:24.526 --> 28:26.352
You can't write that.

28:26.377 --> 28:27.439
I heard they don't even fight.

28:27.463 --> 28:28.581
- Oh.
- [PEOPLE MURMUR]

28:29.246 --> 28:36.246
♪♪

28:36.279 --> 28:43.279
♪♪

28:43.921 --> 28:45.860
It's okay. I-I got this.

28:46.155 --> 28:48.001
[VOICE BREAKING] I can't catch a break.

28:48.891 --> 28:50.641
[SNIFFLES]

28:52.424 --> 28:53.753
- Babe...
- I just need a minute.

28:53.778 --> 28:57.281
♪♪

29:01.272 --> 29:06.899
♪♪

29:06.931 --> 29:10.591
Hey, um... y-your mom's friend
Joyce asked me to get her coat.

29:12.441 --> 29:13.789
I'll be quick.

29:14.665 --> 29:16.744
I should probably get
back out there anyway.

29:16.769 --> 29:18.899
♪♪

29:18.924 --> 29:20.328
[DOOR CLOSES]

29:25.845 --> 29:27.431
You okay?

29:27.680 --> 29:28.799
Yeah.

29:28.824 --> 29:30.916
No. I don't know.

29:31.867 --> 29:34.338
I don't know if this is helpful, but...

29:34.363 --> 29:35.892
[SIGHS]

29:35.917 --> 29:37.845
when we were all out there and...

29:37.870 --> 29:39.494
the minister was reading that prayer,

29:39.519 --> 29:43.869
the... um, the "ashes to
ashes, dust to dust" one,

29:43.894 --> 29:47.541
I was reminded of something I read once.

29:47.800 --> 29:49.588
That nothing lasts forever,

29:51.143 --> 29:55.478
that people we love
sometimes leave our lives,

29:55.752 --> 30:00.283
but what stays is how
they forever changed us.

30:01.095 --> 30:03.103
Are you quoting my screenplay to me?

30:03.128 --> 30:05.205
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY] Maybe.

30:05.468 --> 30:08.220
- [CHUCKLES]
- [DOOR OPENS]

30:08.657 --> 30:11.072
I think it's time for your
brother and me to go home.

30:11.097 --> 30:12.924
Dad, everyone's still here.

30:12.949 --> 30:15.968
Well, if you want, I can just get one
of those share-riding things.

30:17.148 --> 30:18.518
I'll take you home.

30:21.431 --> 30:22.890
Want me to go with you?

30:23.040 --> 30:25.186
I want you to go instead of me.

30:26.596 --> 30:28.405
But I better do it.

30:30.698 --> 30:32.952
[SNIFFLES] Hey, man.

30:33.101 --> 30:34.897
Thank you for being here.

30:35.710 --> 30:37.015
It means a lot.

30:38.628 --> 30:40.186
[SNIFFLES]

30:43.245 --> 30:45.704
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

30:52.279 --> 30:53.866
_

30:53.891 --> 30:57.430
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

31:02.435 --> 31:04.862
_

31:12.948 --> 31:16.011
Just drink that water, son.
You'll feel better tomorrow.

31:16.510 --> 31:17.557
Set your alarm.

31:17.582 --> 31:19.501
You're gonna have to
drive me in the morning.

31:19.743 --> 31:21.628
Your brother's gonna
need to sleep it off.

31:21.653 --> 31:23.862
Hey, Pop, what were you
doing with all this stuff?

31:23.887 --> 31:26.432
I was trying to watch some
old movies of your mother,

31:27.008 --> 31:29.261
but Omar couldn't get
the projector to work.

31:31.675 --> 31:34.004
It helps if you plug it in.

31:34.005 --> 31:36.175
[PROJECTOR WHIRRING]

31:43.109 --> 31:44.650
_

31:44.675 --> 31:46.320
ROME: What is this?

31:46.345 --> 31:48.884
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

31:52.807 --> 31:55.054
♪♪

31:55.055 --> 31:57.003
I'm sure you've been talking to Eddie.

31:57.028 --> 31:59.620
My husband?
Yes, I've been talking to him.

31:59.961 --> 32:02.370
Then maybe you can tell
me what's going on.

32:02.395 --> 32:05.464
You really think that I would
take Charlie away from him,

32:05.489 --> 32:08.528
that I would leave the
country and never come back?

32:08.553 --> 32:11.261
There are a lot of things you've
done that I don't understand.

32:11.961 --> 32:14.040
But what I do understand
is how Eddie feels.

32:14.065 --> 32:16.612
- Katherine...
- Is Eddie Charlie's father?

32:17.841 --> 32:19.393
You know he is.

32:19.689 --> 32:21.971
Then put it on record.

32:22.720 --> 32:24.909
There's a form you and
Eddie can both sign

32:24.934 --> 32:27.964
to correct the mistake you
made on the birth certificate.

32:28.999 --> 32:31.073
I'm sorry, but I can't do that.

32:33.313 --> 32:35.081
Here's the thing.

32:35.180 --> 32:38.503
The reason you're in your house
is because I'm a good lawyer.

32:38.528 --> 32:40.197
So trust me when I tell you

32:40.222 --> 32:42.551
you do not want to go up against me.

32:43.160 --> 32:44.749
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

32:44.774 --> 32:47.198
I know you're a good lawyer, Katherine.

32:47.438 --> 32:49.768
I'm asking you to be a good person.

32:49.793 --> 32:55.198
♪♪

32:55.971 --> 32:57.268
<i>RENEE: Is Rome okay?</i>

32:57.293 --> 32:59.761
<i>Nope. But I'm pretty sure
this surprise I got for him</i>

32:59.786 --> 33:00.955
<i>will help fix that.</i>

33:00.980 --> 33:02.389
[DOOR CLOSES]

33:02.495 --> 33:04.245
<i>Why does Omar get everything?</i>

33:04.270 --> 33:05.346
<i>It's not fair.</i>

33:05.371 --> 33:06.909
<i>He had his choice, and he picked.</i>

33:06.934 --> 33:09.581
<i>Rome, I know how much
you wanted the top bunk.</i>

33:09.606 --> 33:10.975
<i>I really appreciate you</i>

33:11.000 --> 33:12.667
<i>letting your little brother have it.</i>

33:12.692 --> 33:14.315
<i>YOUNG OMAR: Mom, Dad!</i>

33:14.340 --> 33:16.018
<i>It won't flush!</i>

33:16.245 --> 33:17.914
<i>Coming.</i>

33:17.939 --> 33:20.099
<i>I'm never buying that kid LEGOs again.</i>

33:22.854 --> 33:25.063
<i>Hey, Rome, check this out.</i>

33:25.088 --> 33:26.547
[LIGHT SWITCH CLICKS]

33:26.572 --> 33:27.711
[GASPS]

33:27.736 --> 33:29.479
<i>Wow.</i>

33:29.761 --> 33:32.220
<i>Beautiful, isn't it?</i>

33:32.245 --> 33:34.136
<i>So many stars.</i>

33:34.161 --> 33:37.417
<i>Not just stars, sweetheart.
They're constellations.</i>

33:37.442 --> 33:38.901
<i>Constellations?</i>

33:38.926 --> 33:41.464
Omar didn't break
the projector after all.

33:41.769 --> 33:43.378
<i>And when you draw a line between them</i>

33:43.403 --> 33:44.917
<i>like you're connecting dots...</i>

33:45.127 --> 33:47.073
It was you.

33:47.596 --> 33:49.225
What?

33:49.250 --> 33:51.456
The stars I looked up at every night.

33:51.917 --> 33:54.550
I thought it was Mom
who put those there.

33:56.214 --> 33:59.128
We're your parents.
What difference does it make?

33:59.911 --> 34:02.034
It makes a lot of difference.

34:02.767 --> 34:05.534
It makes all the difference, Pop.

34:06.636 --> 34:08.870
When we buried Mom today,

34:09.853 --> 34:12.228
I meant it when I said
there was nothing more

34:12.254 --> 34:14.393
that she and I needed
to say to each other.

34:16.522 --> 34:19.728
But I can't say that
about you and me, Pop.

34:21.007 --> 34:25.467
We have so much crap that we
still need to work through.

34:27.136 --> 34:29.853
But seeing this,
seeing how you showed up for me,

34:29.879 --> 34:30.987
it just makes me think, you know,

34:31.012 --> 34:33.768
maybe we can figure it out somehow.

34:36.127 --> 34:38.051
But when I don't know that
you're doing things for me,

34:38.074 --> 34:39.706
I can't help but think that...

34:40.346 --> 34:42.697
you don't have my back.

34:43.456 --> 34:45.636
That nurturing crap...

34:46.617 --> 34:49.197
was always your mother's department.

34:50.047 --> 34:52.007
And I guess with her gone...

34:54.456 --> 34:55.534
... there are a lot of things

34:55.559 --> 34:57.925
we're gonna have to
figure out how to do.

35:01.491 --> 35:03.557
I'm gonna need you, son.

35:03.582 --> 35:09.136
♪♪

35:09.161 --> 35:10.161
Good.

35:13.073 --> 35:15.245
'Cause I'm gonna need you, too, Pop.

35:15.270 --> 35:22.270
♪♪

35:22.295 --> 35:25.096
<i>Who knew the bottom bunk was so awesome?</i>

35:25.121 --> 35:26.160
[SIGHS]

35:26.185 --> 35:28.268
I should finish packing.

35:28.293 --> 35:30.362
♪♪

35:30.387 --> 35:32.465
<i>... our little secret. You got it.</i>

35:33.105 --> 35:34.862
<i>Good night, Romy.</i>

35:34.887 --> 35:36.988
<i>You'll always be my sweet boy.</i>

35:37.013 --> 35:41.132
♪♪

35:41.157 --> 35:43.037
[TAPE FLAPPING]

35:44.714 --> 35:46.440
Good night, Mom.

35:53.187 --> 35:55.346
- Hey, Gare?
- That's my name.

35:55.371 --> 35:56.558
[CLEARS THROAT]

35:56.583 --> 35:59.293
[CHUCKLES] What is this?

35:59.318 --> 36:01.567
It's totally professional, right?

36:01.592 --> 36:03.605
You like it?
Or do you think it's too much?

36:03.630 --> 36:05.387
We can lose the photo of Prince Harry.

36:05.412 --> 36:07.793
[LAUGHS] I cannot believe you did this.

36:07.818 --> 36:09.566
Oh, but wait. There's more, folks.

36:09.591 --> 36:11.019
I was gonna get you a powdered wig,

36:11.044 --> 36:14.373
but then, believe it or not,
I had a better idea.

36:14.643 --> 36:16.691
Oh, my.

36:19.268 --> 36:20.897
- It's a bob.
- [CHUCKLES]

36:20.922 --> 36:22.996
Nothing says Oxford like a bob.

36:23.021 --> 36:24.653
That's what the lady
at the wig store says.

36:24.677 --> 36:26.543
I hope you like it
'cause all sales are final

36:26.568 --> 36:28.466
and you know Colin's not
gonna wear that damn thing.

36:28.490 --> 36:30.529
Wow. I love it.

36:30.690 --> 36:33.472
Well, when you first told
me about the fellowship...

36:33.833 --> 36:36.402
I acted like a real
[BRITISH ACCENT] wanker.

36:36.860 --> 36:38.683
[NORMAL VOICE] That
means "jerk" in English.

36:38.708 --> 36:40.668
- Yeah.
- I Googled it.

36:40.693 --> 36:44.738
And then something Omar said
actually got me to thinking.

36:44.763 --> 36:46.246
Stasia and her weird sex stuff?

36:46.271 --> 36:47.942
At first, yes.
That's all I could think about.

36:47.966 --> 36:51.121
No, that TV show that you
two were talking about.

36:52.503 --> 36:54.277
I mean, it makes sense.

36:54.955 --> 36:58.543
I wanted us to grow
in the same direction.

36:58.568 --> 37:02.965
So, if you want to...
you want to go to Oxford, then...

37:03.711 --> 37:05.949
I want you to go to Oxford.

37:08.020 --> 37:10.824
♪♪

37:10.849 --> 37:11.979
Thank you.

37:14.455 --> 37:16.535
This really means a lot to me.

37:21.760 --> 37:25.152
Just promise me that you won't
get behind the wheel over there.

37:25.477 --> 37:28.266
You can barely handle
the right side of the road.

37:28.291 --> 37:29.902
[LAUGHS]

37:34.523 --> 37:35.772
Everyone leave?

37:35.797 --> 37:37.166
Pretty much.

37:37.425 --> 37:40.168
Delilah's bringing some
things down from the roof.

37:40.193 --> 37:43.379
[EXHALES SHARPLY] I was hoping
to talk to PJ.

37:43.404 --> 37:45.207
I didn't even see him leave.

37:45.232 --> 37:47.232
I'm sure you can talk to him tomorrow.

37:48.331 --> 37:51.040
Right now, I'm worried about you.

37:51.424 --> 37:52.840
I know you are.

37:52.986 --> 37:54.815
I know everyone is.

37:54.840 --> 37:56.308
I'm not gonna lie.

37:56.720 --> 38:00.035
I haven't felt this low in a while.

38:01.792 --> 38:04.246
But it's not the same as before, Gina.

38:04.271 --> 38:08.972
You know, my mom just died.
I'm supposed to feel... sad.

38:10.126 --> 38:14.254
But... I know that I'm gonna
feel a little better tomorrow

38:14.279 --> 38:16.637
and a little better
the day after that, and...

38:18.946 --> 38:22.035
It's not the same.
It's different this time.

38:24.031 --> 38:26.090
I know I'm gonna get through this.

38:26.115 --> 38:27.944
We gonna get through this.

38:27.969 --> 38:28.969
Mm.

38:30.696 --> 38:36.461
♪♪

38:36.486 --> 38:37.826
[SIGHS]

38:42.711 --> 38:45.242
♪♪

38:45.267 --> 38:48.383
- _
- Okay, T, get into your pajamas.

38:48.408 --> 38:50.118
Dad's gonna read you a story.

39:01.761 --> 39:03.009
[SMOOCHES]

39:04.619 --> 39:08.923
Actually, T, I'm gonna
read you a story tonight.

39:08.948 --> 39:10.228
Ha ha ha.

39:12.462 --> 39:16.048
These are the last of the
platters from the roof.

39:16.073 --> 39:18.283
I'm gonna go home, check in on Soph.

39:18.308 --> 39:21.127
Yeah, is she okay? She seemed upset.

39:21.152 --> 39:23.548
Yeah, she and PJ just...

39:23.573 --> 39:25.111
Young love.

39:25.421 --> 39:27.697
They'll figure it out.

39:27.913 --> 39:29.532
You've had a long day.

39:29.557 --> 39:31.056
Don't worry about us.

39:31.081 --> 39:33.142
Um... I'll call you tomorrow.

39:33.167 --> 39:34.207
Mm-hmm.

39:35.028 --> 39:36.767
Give Rome a kiss.

39:38.757 --> 39:40.384
[DOOR OPENS]

39:41.335 --> 39:42.335
ROME: Gina?

39:42.360 --> 39:44.009
Should I have said something?

39:44.034 --> 39:46.572
'Cause I-I'm a feeling a little guilty.

39:47.768 --> 39:49.213
- What's wrong?
- The DNA test,

39:49.238 --> 39:50.369
it was under the bed.

39:51.111 --> 39:52.531
It's gone.

39:53.846 --> 39:55.354
[ELEVATOR BELL DINGS]

39:57.559 --> 39:58.967
Mitch.

39:58.992 --> 40:00.494
What are you doing here?

40:00.626 --> 40:03.596
Um, uh, my friend's mom died, and I...

40:03.884 --> 40:05.197
Why are you here?

40:05.222 --> 40:08.260
I'm looking for my son.
Have you seen Patrick?

40:11.581 --> 40:13.127
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

40:13.152 --> 40:19.096
♪♪

40:19.121 --> 40:21.201
PJ's Barbara Morgan's son?

40:23.300 --> 40:25.049
Why didn't you tell me?

40:25.074 --> 40:28.679
♪♪

